s Core Curriculum Faculty Information System Faculty Success Forms and Templates Preventing and Resolving Workplace Issues Recruitment and Compensation Research Resources for Faculty Tenure and Promotion UNT Employee Guide UNT Policy Office More UNT Faculty and Staff Resources HomeFaculty Recruitment For Applicants to Tenure/Tenure-Track Faculty Positions, Lecturers, Librarians, and Research Professionals Apply for faculty job positions The Faculty Recruitment System at the University of North Texas is designed to provide faster processing of employment information, deliver up-to-date access to information regarding job postings, and allow for more detailed screenings of Applicants' qualifications before they reach the interview stage. The system can be used to view applicants to your postings and change and monitor the status of an applicant through the hiring process.  The following titles are advertised with this system: Regular Faculty Librarians Academic Administrators Professional Research Other Faculty Recruitment Resources Faculty Hiring Process Step-by-Step Faculty Hiring System Departmental User's Guide Faculty Hiring Team Professional Research Hiring Process Login to PeopleAdmin Faculty Jobs to manage positions and applicants Research Cluster Hiring Steps Faculty Recruitment and Hiring Expenses Reimbursement Job Description for Research Professor/Research Scientist/Postdoctoral Research Scientist Titles Adjunct Recruitment Resources Adjunct Hiring Process Step-by-Step Adjunct Hiring Process Presentation Adjunct Recruitment Request Form Contact us at facultyjobs@unt.edu for any questions or concerns. Visit Us   Office of the Provost and VP for Academic Affairs370 Hurley Administration Building Mail Us   University of North TexasOffice of the Provost and VP for Academic Affairs 1155 Union Circle #311190 Denton, Texas 76203-5017 [map]   Contact Us   940-565-2550 TTY: 940-369-8652 FAX: 940-565-2774 For questions about this website, contact ronda.bewley@unt.ed